   127	## Decision 2 — chromatograms ground-truth shapes
   128	
   129	Verified by pyarrow dump of `refs/mzPeak/small.unpacked.mzpeak/chromatograms_{data,metadata}.parquet`.
   130	
   131	### `chromatograms_data.parquet`
   132	
   133	Schema (field order is load-bearing — match exactly):
   134	
   135	```
   136	point: struct<chromatogram_index: uint64, time: double, intensity: float, ms_level: int64>
   137	```
   138	
   139	- **1 chromatogram** (chromatogram_index distribution: `{0: 48}`), **48 points** = 48 scans.
   140	- `time`: f64, **minutes**, == per-scan RT.
   141	- `intensity`: f32, device TIC value per scan.
   142	- `ms_level`: **i64, the per-scan ms_level** (distribution `{1: 14, 2: 34}`). **NOT 0, NOT fixed 1.**
   143	- Per-child field metadata (drives the `chromatogram_array_index` KV, below):
   144	  - `time`: data_type `MS:1000523`, array_type `MS:1000595` (time array), unit `UO:0000031`, sorting_rank 0
   145	  - `intensity`: data_type `MS:1000521`, array_type `MS:1000515`, unit `MS:1000131`
   146	  - `ms_level`: data_type `MS:1000522`, array_type `MS:1000786` (non-standard data array), unit `UO:0000186`
   147	- Footer KV: `chromatogram_array_index` (JSON, prefix "chunk"... actually `"prefix":"point"`),
   148	  `chromatogram_data_point_count`, plus the same file-level metadata blocks
   149	  (`run`/`software_list`/`file_description`/`instrument_configuration_list`/`data_processing_method_list`/`sample_list`/`scan_settings_list`).
   150	  Observed `chromatogram_data_point_count` = `0` in the reference (a known reference quirk; our
   151	  spectra facets already write `"0"` here too — keep parity).
   152	
   153	The exact `chromatogram_array_index` JSON to emit (verbatim from ground truth):
   154	
   155	```json
   156	{"prefix":"point","entries":[
   157	 {"context":"chromatogram","path":"point.time","data_type":"MS:1000523","array_type":"MS:1000595","array_name":"time array","unit":"UO:0000031","buffer_format":"point","buffer_priority":"primary","sorting_rank":0},
   158	 {"context":"chromatogram","path":"point.intensity","data_type":"MS:1000521","array_type":"MS:1000515","array_name":"intensity array","unit":"MS:1000131","buffer_format":"point","buffer_priority":"primary"},
   159	 {"context":"chromatogram","path":"point.ms_level","data_type":"MS:1000522","array_type":"MS:1000786","array_name":"ms level","unit":"UO:0000186","buffer_format":"point","buffer_priority":"primary"}
   160	]}
   161	```
   162	(The reference serializes `transform:null`/`data_processing_id:null`/`sorting_rank:null` on the 2nd/3rd
   163	entries; our writer omits null keys in `SpectrumArrayIndex` and still passes the validator, so omit them.)
   164	
   165	### `chromatograms_metadata.parquet`
   166	
   167	Three top-level struct columns (`chromatogram`, `precursor`, `selected_ion`) — same packed-parallel
   168	shape as spectra_metadata. **1 row.** The `precursor`/`selected_ion` structs are **present-but-null**
