   205	## Decision 3 — index + cv_list deltas
   206	
   207	**DECISION:** Add the two chromatogram entries to `files[]` and route the new chromatogram column
   208	accessions through the existing `Cv()` collector. No cv_list version bump or new schema needed.
   209	
   210	### `mzpeak_index.json` `files[]` — add (verified ground-truth entries):
   211	
   212	```json
   213	{"name":"chromatograms_metadata.parquet","entity_type":"chromatogram","data_kind":"metadata"},
   214	{"name":"chromatograms_data.parquet","entity_type":"chromatogram","data_kind":"data arrays"}
   215	```
   216	
   217	(Ground-truth ordering puts metadata before data; order is not validator-significant.) Extend
   218	`BuildIndex` (`MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:1043-1083`) to append these when chromatograms are written.
   219	
   220	### CV accessions that must flow into the generated cv_list
   221	
   222	The generated cv_list is collected from every accession routed through `Cv()`/`CvParam()`/`JParam()`
   223	into `_cvPrefixes` (`MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:565-577`, 871-893). New accessions introduced by
   224	chromatograms:
   225	
   226	| Accession | Where it appears | Prefix already covered? |
   227	|-----------|------------------|--------------------------|
   228	| `MS:1000235` | chromatogram_type **cell value** | MS — yes (cell value, NOT inflected by validator anyway) |
   229	| `MS:1000626` | `chromatogram_type` **column name** | MS — yes |
   230	| `MS:1000465` | `scan_polarity` column name (chromatogram) | MS — yes (already used by spectra) |
   231	| `MS:1003060` | `number_of_data_points` column name | MS — yes (already used) |
   232	| `MS:1000595` `MS:1000786` `MS:1000522` `MS:1000521` `MS:1000515` | data-facet **field metadata** only | not inflected by validator (see below) |
   233	| `UO:0000031` `UO:0000186` `MS:1000131` | data-facet field metadata / column units | UO/MS — yes |
   234	
   235	**cv_list outcome:** Only `{MS, UO}` are referenced — exactly the set Phase 3 already declares. **No
   236	new CV prefix, no version bump.** Continue to route `MS:1000626`/`MS:1000235`/`MS:1000465` etc.
   237	through `Cv()`/`CvParam()` so the assert-coverage logic stays exhaustive (defensive — even though
   238	{MS,UO} are already present).
   239	
   240	### Validator chromatogram-specific checks (from `~/Claude/mzPeakValidator`)
   241	
   242	Authoritative source: `mzpeak_validator/profiles/mzpeak-0.9/rules/{structural,cv}.rules.json`,
   243	`core.py`.
   244	
   245	- **There is NO `chromatograms_metadata.columns.json`** — no `columns_present` rule for chromatograms.
   246	  (`schema/tables/` contains only `spectra_{data,metadata,peaks}.columns.json`.)
   247	- `data_kind_has_facet` gates `entity_types: ["spectrum","mass spectrum"]` only
   248	  (`structural.rules.json:21`) — the chromatogram `data arrays` entry is **not** checked for a `point`
   249	  facet. (It still has one, harmlessly.)
   250	- `cv_inflection_chromatograms_metadata` (`cv.rules.json:18-20`) inflects only **column names** in
   251	  `chromatograms_metadata` matching `${CV}_${digits}_...`. The chromatogram columns
   252	  (`MS_1000465_...`, `MS_1000626_...`, `MS_1003060_...`) all resolve in the pinned MS OBO → no error.
   253	  The `MS:1000235` value lives in a **cell**, not a column name → not inflected.
   254	- `cv_list_declared` (`cv.rules.json:22-24`, `core.py:573-589`) scans `chromatograms_metadata` column
   255	  names for CV codes and requires each in `metadata.cv_list`. Codes are MS/UO → already declared.
   256	- The data-facet field-metadata accessions (`MS:1000595` etc.) are **not** scanned by any rule
   257	  (cv_inflection reads logical column/leaf names, not Arrow child field metadata) — verified by
   258	  reading `core.py::p_cv_inflection` and `_used_cv_codes`.
   259	
   260	**Net: adding chromatograms introduces zero new failing rule. 0/0 is preserved** (assuming the
   261	metadata facet exists whenever chromatograms are present — the only chromatogram precondition, which
   262	we satisfy by always writing both facets together).
