   268	
   269	## Decision 4 — Differential harness vs mzML2mzPeak (VER-02)
   270	
   271	**DECISION:** Use the **prebuilt arm64 binary** at `~/Claude/mzML2mzPeak/target/release/mzml2mzpeak`
   272	(it already exists — `file` confirms `Mach-O 64-bit executable arm64`). **Do NOT rebuild in-plan**
   273	(cargo release build of a Rust 1.96 / mzdata tree is heavy/slow; the binary runs correctly — verified
   274	`--help` and a real conversion). Provide a one-line fallback build only if the binary is missing.
   275	
   276	### Build (only if binary absent)
   277	
   278	```bash
   279	cd ~/Claude/mzML2mzPeak && cargo build --release    # rust-toolchain.toml pins 1.96; binary -> target/release/mzml2mzpeak
   280	```
   281	
   282	### Exact reference pipeline (verified end-to-end, all three steps run clean)
   283	
   284	```bash
   285	DLL=ThermoRawFileParser/bin/x64/Release/net8.0/ThermoRawFileParser.dll
   286	RAW=ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/Data/small.RAW
   287	M2M=~/Claude/mzML2mzPeak/target/release/mzml2mzpeak
   288	
   289	# 1) RAW -> PROFILE mzML  (-f 1 = mzML; -p = noPeakPicking => profile, aligns with our spectra_data)
   290	arch -x86_64 ~/.dotnet-x64/dotnet "$DLL" -i "$RAW" -b /tmp/p4/small.profile.mzML -f 1 -p
   291	
   292	# 2) mzML -> reference mzpeak  (--no-numpress => lossless m/z, chunk-delta not numpress)
   293	"$M2M" /tmp/p4/small.profile.mzML /tmp/p4/small.ref.mzpeak --no-numpress
   294	
   295	# 3) RAW -> our TRFP mzpeak   (-f 4 = MzPeak;  NOTE: 4 not 5 — 5 is None)
